January 26, 2026: 
- Initialized the directory. Downloaded gcc and make.
- Setup main and the added populate_board and draw_board methods to initialize and view the board.
- Created the tour method to take in only x and y as paramaters and print out the path for that certain starting point.
- For the tour method, I had a basic approach of +-2 for x and y without any step counter.
- The current approach only returned one path. It did not yet include backtracking (I realise this mistake the next day.)
- Created CHANGELOGS and Makefile.

January 27, 2026:
- Went to TA help hours and this is when I found out I had to print all 1728 tours and not just 1.
- Added loops to go through all the different starting points on the 5x5 grid.
- Updated the tour method to keep a track on steps.
- Added backtracking by storing the board[x][y] in a temp value and then setting it back after the knight's movement
- Used the recursive approach for tour.
- Added a counter to display the total number of tours.
- Updated Makefile to include -g flag and clean rule for pyrite compatibility.